com.ust.lib.jsqlparser.statement.upsert

Class Upsert

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ust.lib.jsqlparser.statement.upsert.Upsert
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Statement

    public class Upsert
extends Object
implements Statement
    The UPSERT INTO statement. This statement is basically the combination of "insert" and "update". That means it will operate inserts if not present and updates otherwise the value in the table. Note the values modified will be either a list of values or a select statement. Here is the documentation of the grammar of this operation: http://phoenix.apache.org/language/#upsert_values http://phoenix.apache.org/language/#upsert_select
    Author:
    messfish
